#: ../../source/example_gallery/fluid/cavity_3d.rst:2
#: 7ee70cd9c25c466b9f2d2f157a04428c
msgid "3D Lid-Driven Cavity"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/example_gallery/fluid/cavity_3d.rst:4
#: dd992482f74d41b0a847bfac865389b4
#, python-brace-format
msgid ""
"The 3D extension of the 2D cavity benchmark. The geometry is a unit cube "
":math:`(0, 1)^3` filled with fluid; the top face slides at unit speed in "
"the :math:`x` direction; all other faces enforce no-slip. The script "
"``examples/fluid/cavity_3d/cavity_3d.py`` solves the steady "
"incompressible Navier-Stokes system at :math:`\\mathrm{Re} = 100` on a "
"tetrahedral mesh."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/example_gallery/fluid/cavity_3d.rst:11
#: 1ef0b1e3abd64bf5a6b07441cd196da1
msgid ""
"Because the underlying ``NavierStokesAssembler`` (see :doc:`cavity`) is "
"**dimension-generic** — it takes the spatial dimension from "
"``gradu.shape[0]`` and stamps a ``(dim+1) × (dim+1)`` block at each "
"quadrature point — switching from 2D to 3D is essentially a mesh swap and"
" a slightly larger DOF mask. There is no separate \"3D solver\"."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/example_gallery/fluid/cavity_3d.rst:20
#: 5dd1c2a50b914c75a8ea1a097a0baa64
msgid "Problem"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/example_gallery/fluid/cavity_3d.rst:22
#: 9a2818f3de7b43df9c3a7b364513ccdd
#, python-brace-format
msgid ""
"\\rho\\, (\\mathbf{u} \\cdot \\nabla)\\mathbf{u}\n"
"\\;=\\; -\\nabla p + \\mu\\, \\Delta \\mathbf{u}\n"
"\\quad \\text{in } \\Omega = (0, 1)^3,\n"
"\\qquad\n"
"\\nabla \\cdot \\mathbf{u} \\;=\\; 0,"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/example_gallery/fluid/cavity_3d.rst:30
#: 66797680378746459d8bc673751b9c2a
#, python-brace-format
msgid ""
"with :math:`\\rho = 1`, :math:`\\mu = 1/\\mathrm{Re}`, and boundary "
"conditions"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/example_gallery/fluid/cavity_3d.rst:33
#: 01f79d1fd949481e880d8a1d3e3f7027
#, python-brace-format
msgid "top face (:math:`y = 1`): :math:`\\mathbf{u} = (1, 0, 0)`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/example_gallery/fluid/cavity_3d.rst:34
#: 2976b1c46a1f4b3bb37ff3692140fcde
#, python-brace-format
msgid "other faces: :math:`\\mathbf{u} = \\mathbf{0}` (no-slip)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/example_gallery/fluid/cavity_3d.rst:35
#: fe38d9b3a23d43e89f2ed0c10d5fa905
msgid "one node: :math:`p = 0` (pressure pin)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/example_gallery/fluid/cavity_3d.rst:39
#: 90da7ddd81db436ba239b9b40f004c62
msgid "What changes from 2D"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/example_gallery/fluid/cavity_3d.rst:41
#: c8d68d722c764fefa02561448a5aeb1c
msgid ""
"``Mesh.gen_cube(chara_length=…, element_type=\"tet\")`` replaces "
"``Mesh.gen_rectangle``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/example_gallery/fluid/cavity_3d.rst:43
#: 7425e9cdc61643a6ab1acca9f1a0457f
msgid ""
"The DOF layout is per-node ``[u, v, w, p]`` instead of ``[u, v, p]``: 4 "
"DOFs per node × ``n_points``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/example_gallery/fluid/cavity_3d.rst:45
#: 1a4862e3481e475cae5fd71c18080735
msgid ""
"The lid mask now picks faces of the cube (``mesh.points[:, 1] > 1 - "
"eps``) rather than edges of the square."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/example_gallery/fluid/cavity_3d.rst:48
#: d84109d66dcd4ddcaec8d1d8abd199c5
msgid ""
"The output is volumetric: ``cavity_3d.vtu`` for ParaView, plus cross-"
"section slices at :math:`z = 0.5` rendered via PyVista as "
"``cavity_3d.png``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/example_gallery/fluid/cavity_3d.rst:52
#: be03497ab0654972ac84e79240a42932
msgid ""
"Everything else — the Picard loop, the SUPG/PSPG stamp, the pressure pin,"
" the use of :class:`~tensormesh.Condenser` — is identical to "
":doc:`cavity`. The same ``NavierStokesAssembler`` class works in both "
"cases:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/example_gallery/fluid/cavity_3d.rst:57
#: 2db87d82a7f3437a930caa11d5a8d124
msgid "examples/fluid/cavity_3d/cavity_3d.py (essence)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/example_gallery/fluid/cavity_3d.rst:72
#: fd05202b68a743c1a541fa3c070590c2
#, python-brace-format
msgid ""
"The 4-DOFs-per-node layout means the resulting linear system is roughly "
":math:`(4 n_\\text{nodes})^2` in nonzero count — at ``chara_length=0.05``"
" that is on the order of a million unknowns, so a GPU backend "
"(``backend=\"cudss\"`` or ``\"pytorch\"``, see "
":doc:`../../user_guide/linear_solvers`) is recommended once you go beyond"
" a few thousand nodes."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/example_gallery/fluid/cavity_3d.rst:79
#: 8180bd05bac9496a9cdecde762879a00
msgid "3D lid-driven cavity speed and pressure on the z=0.5 mid-plane"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/example_gallery/fluid/cavity_3d.rst:83
#: 438982588de94901b5b20f6e71ff5052
msgid ""
"Output of ``cavity_3d.py``: speed magnitude (left) and pressure (right) "
"on the :math:`z=0.5` mid-plane slice through the cube. The flow pattern "
"matches the 2D solution near the lid but decays toward the front and back"
" walls — the picture at the mid-plane therefore shows weaker "
"recirculation than the strict-2D case. Full 3D fields are written to "
"``cavity_3d.vtu`` for ParaView."
msgstr ""

